items.sentence: I don't think that Tom really did that by himself.
I don't think that Tom realizes how young Mary is.
I don't think that Tom needs to worry about money.
I don't think that Tom meant what he said to Mary.
I don't think that Tom knows why Mary isn't happy.
I don't think that you should follow Tom's advice.
I don't think that we're going to need Tom's help.
I don't think we'll ever know what Tom really did.
I don't think we should leave until Tom gets here.
I don't think that Tom would mind if you did that.
